ROOM REVIEW APP
===============

This is designed (I use the word loosely) as a static site
with a Flask app for the bits which can't be done statically.

Prereqs:
Some way to run Flask web apps
Mysql
Python MySQLdb or pymysql module

How to set up

1. Set up the database. You can use review_setup_db for this.
2. Insert any pre-existing data into the database.
3. Update config.py with your own database credentials
4. Create a target folder in public_html with a 'rooms' subfolder
5. Edit update.sh to point to this target folder, and generate the room files.
6. Use homepage.py to generate the homepage
7. Set up the .htaccess to require Raven for access and login in the target folder.
8. Set up the web app. I used the example run-python.sh script from /public/societies/sample/, and a .htaccess in the root of public_html/ to set a request header with the value of $REMOTE_USER, as well as forwarding the requests to a socket. Refer to https://docs.srcf.net/reference/web-hosting/web-applications/. I did the systemd option
9. Add update.sh to your crontab to update the files regularly.

Note you will need to update the homepage manually - but cron mail should remind you of this fact.

Note also: you may want to check your database is set to use UTF-8 by default.

Andrew Jenkins 2023-12-28